description: Recently sold: $445,000. Country living at its finest!  Fenced and ready for the horses!!  18 scenic rolling acres set on Buffalo Creek.  One of a kind two story loaded with character and charm, graciously set back on the lot.  Sprawling main level with 2 separate family rooms, center island kitchen, formal dining with built-ins, main floor laundry, mud room, bedroom/den, 2 bathrooms, huge deck, and a 3 season porch!  Upstairs features 3 large bedrooms, 2 additional baths, owners suite with fireplace and private bath.  Additional upstairs multi-use bonus room with private entrance, could be a great mother-in-law suite.  The walkout lower level was excavated in 2002 with extra course of block allowing high ceilings and natural light, featuring finished bedroom, rough-in bath, lots of storage, and endless possibilities for finishing. Enjoy incredible views of the spectacular setting from nearly every room in the house. Attached 3 car, extra deep, heated garage with floor drain.  Newer 57 x 33 outbuilding with concrete floor, bar, great man cave, storage, shop, etc.  Outdoor wood burning boiler efficiently cuts heating bills way down.

description: Recently sold: $310,000. Immaculate walk out rambler on meticulously maintained double lot on east side of Norwood Young America.  Quiet area but with easy access to Hwy 212.  Enjoy sunsets from light and bright porch.  Home has a heated, over sized attached garage as well as a 3 car detached on 2nd lot.  Open yet livable plan is ideal for those wanting a one level with intimate space. Granite kitchen counters, tiled back splashes and ample seating on the main floor. The lower level has a rec room with a smart fireplace, a abundant hobby room that could work as a bedroom, a bath and another BR.  The yard looks like a master gardener has been taking care of it.  It is possible to sub-divide the 2nd lot relatively easy.  Easy home for discerning buyers to fall in love with.
